definitions.definition: A Eurasian sparrowhawk , Accipiter nisus , a small, short-winged European hawk that preys on smaller birds.

subdefinitions.definition: A female such bird, a male being a musket .

definitions.definition: Any of numerous other relatively small birds of Old World species of Accipiter , that prey on smaller birds or otherwise resemble A. nisus .
Alternative form of sparrow hawk ; American kestrel , Falco sparverius , of similar size and habit.
